lead_paragraph: On Tuesday night, at about the halfway point in the current season of ABC's "Dancing With the Stars," the judges and viewers voted to eliminate Chaz Bono. But not before he had become, as one gay rights media advocacy group put it, "the world's most well-known transgender person."

headline.main: Victory Eludes Chaz Bono, but Not Fame
